  <h1>Community & Support Resources</h1>

  <div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Purpose:</strong> Connect with veteran service dog communities, find training-friendly locations, navigate public access advocacy, and build a support network for your training journey
  </div>

  <h2>Why Community Matters</h2>

  <p>Training a service dog is isolating. You'll face public access challenges, training frustrations, and questions nobody else seems to understand. Connecting with other veteran service dog handlers - especially those training pitbulls or bully breeds - provides invaluable support, practical advice, and validation that you're not alone in this journey.</p>

  <div class="alert alert-warning">
    <strong>Reality Check:</strong> Training a pitbull service dog comes with unique challenges. You'll face discrimination, access denials, and negative reactions based solely on breed. Having a community who understands this struggle is not just helpful - it's essential for mental health and perseverance.
  </div>

